ce:section.ce:para:
The highest PCE of PSCs is observed in the SnO2-GQDs ETL with PCE of 17.81%, open voltage circuit (V

                           oc
                        ) of 1.02 V, and maximum current density generated (J

                           sc
                        ) of 22.33 mA/cm2, with an optimized Fill factor (FF) of 79.98%. Moreover, the PCE of SnO2-citric ETL is higher than that of unmodified SnO2 ETL. Thus, the enhancement of PCE is observed for both approaches of adding citric acid and GQDs. The increase of FF by the surface modification of SnO2 film with citric acid (78.83%) and GQDs (79.98%) compared to unmodified SnO2 film at 75.53% can be observed and maybe due to the carboxyl group from citric acid and GQDs which can modify the defects on the SnO2 ETL surface resulting in lower series resistance (R

                           serie
                        ), and higher shunt resistance (R

                           shunt
                        ). Also, the low hysteresis index (HI) is obtained from the surface modification of SnO2 ETL with citric acid and GQDs, suggesting the enhancement of the overall performance of PSCs by surface modification. Although the increment of fill factor after the modified SnO2 with citric acid and GQDs is quite small, the stability (as seen in Fig. 7) of SnO2-GQDs ETLs exhibits a significant improvement compared to those of SnO2-citric or the unmodified SnO2. For commercialization, photoconversion efficiency and stability are both crucial factors.
